    {
      "id": "049ab71f_78fbdfbe",
      "file_path": "models-tosca/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/tosca/authorative/concepts/ToscaConceptIdentifierOptVersion.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 43,
      "message": "OK, I have tried a different approach.\n\nIt would be nice to create a subclass of ToscaConceptIdentifierOptVersion that would handle the different names for serialization/deserialization of the policy identifier name/version \"policy-id\" and \"policy-version\" used on the PAP-PDP communication. However, this can't be done  because the only name to change the @SerializedName would to be to introduce new name/version fields on the subclass and this would shadow the name/version fields in the base class.\n\nSo what I ahve done instead is to introduce a new class called PapPolicyIdentifier in models-pap. This class acts as a serialization/deserialization class for the ToscaConceptIdentifierOptVersion class. It is used to serialize and deserailze the messages on the PAP/PDP communication and is used as the members on the PdpDeployPolicies class. Have a look at that class to see what you think of that.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2021-01-05 13:52:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "54331e20_fd006651",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
